               <listBibl type="secondary">
                  <bibl>
                     <ptr target="bm:Smidt2010EnAeTegray"/>
                  </bibl>
                  <bibl xml:id="Lusini">
                     <ptr target="bm:Lusini2005EAEHawzen"/>
                  </bibl>
               </listBibl>
               <note>
                  <ab type="description">Ḥawzen is the name both of a waradā and of its administrative
                     capital. This area was already important in Aksumite times and maintained an
                     important role also after the decline of Aksum. Its territory was often and for
                     long periods of time subject to historical <placeName ref="LOC6569Tegray"
                        >Tǝgrāy</placeName>'s control.</ab>
                    <ab type="tabot">Still preserved in the modern town of Ḥawzen
                     is a three-aisled rock-hewn church possibly dating to the 10th-13th century
                     with a sanctuary containing a tābot dedicated to <roleName type="title"
                        >ʾAbuna</roleName>
                       <persName ref="PRS9162TaklaHa" type="tabot">Takla Hāymānot</persName>.</ab>
               </note>
            </place>
         </listPlace>
